You look off into the distance to the west.
You see the train line continue far west, past your
origin point.  You see a vast desert, with a small
glint of some sort of structure in the middle.
How did you get within viewing distance of a desert?
Where ARE you?
You look off into the distance to the southwest.
You can see the train line snake through the trees
and back to Boardwalk Station.  You can just barely
see Spection Tower.
You wish you could place it on a map.
Where ARE you?
You look off into the distance to the south.
You can see the train line snake back to the Downda
Isles, your previous destination.
You struggle to think of a place with mountains so
close to the ocean.
Where ARE you?
You look off into the distance to the east.
There's nothing but water as far as the eye can see.
The horizon is a perfectly straight line dividing
sky and sea.  It's beautiful.
Even the color of the water is unfamiliar.
Where ARE you?
